Package gov.nist.secauto.metaschema.model.common

Provides interfaces, abstract implementation classes, and exceptions that are used in Metaschema APIs.
  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    IAssembly
    A marker interface for an information element that is an assembly model type.
    IAssemblyDefinition  
    IAssemblyInstance  
    IChoice
    A marker interface for a choice between multiple Metaschema instances.
    IChoiceInstance
    This marker interface represents a choice of allowed instances in a Metachema.
    IDefinition  
    IField
    A marker interface for an information element that is a field model type.
    IFieldDefinition  
    IFieldInstance  
    IFlag
    A marker interface for an information element that is an flag model type.
    IFlagDefinition  
    IFlagInstance  
    IInlineNamedDefinition<INSTANCE extends INamedInstance>
    A trait indicating that the implementation is a localized definition that is declared in-line as an instance.
    IInstance
    This marker interface indicates that this object is an instance.
    IMetaschema
    The API for accessing information about a given Metaschema.
    IModelContainer
    Indicates that the Metaschema definition type has a complex model that can contain flags, field, and assembly instances.
    IModelElement
    A marker interface for Metaschema constructs that can be members of a Metaschema definition's model.
    IModelInstance
    This marker interface is used to identify a field or assembly instance that is a member of an assembly's model.
    INamedDefinition
    This marker interface is used for some collections that contain various named definitions.
    INamedInstance
    This marker interface indicates that the instance has a flag, field, or assembly name associated with it which will be used in JSON/YAML or XML to identify the data.
    INamedModelDefinition
    This marker interface identifies a definition that is intended to be part of an Assembly's model.
    INamedModelElement
    A marker interface for Metaschema constructs that can be members of a Metaschema definition's model that are named.
    INamedModelInstance  
    INamedValuedDefinition
    This marker interface is used for some collections that contain various named definitions that have an associated value.
    IRootAssemblyDefinition  
    IValuedDefinition
    This marker interface identifies Metaschema definition types that have associated values (i.e., field, flag).
